Class ImagePlusHyp

java.lang.Object
  ij.ImagePlus
      jclustering.ImagePlusHyp
All Implemented Interfaces:
ij.measure.Measurements, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.lang.Cloneable
public class ImagePlusHyp
extends ij.ImagePlus

This class extends ImagePlus in order to add a handy getTAC(int, int, int) method that allows to easily grab time-activity curves.

Author:
José María Mateos.

getTAC

public double[] getTAC(int x,
                       int y,
                       int slice)
Gets the time-activity curve (dixel, after "dynamic pixel") for the given coordinates.

Parameters:
x - The x coordinate of the desired dixel.
y - The y coordinate of the desired dixel.
slice - Slice (1-based) of the desired dixel.
Returns:
A double array containing the values for the given voxel on each frame, or null if the coordinates are not valid.
